    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e5ed2ec3_a202e7f7",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/specs/specs.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 483,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-12-18T19:08:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "nit: Is there any reason not to GOB-encode the entire TaskCfg into a single cell? If we\u0027re worried about size limits, I think we\u0027re going to see problems in TaskScheduler due to patching tasks.json and processing all the tasks long before we reach the 100MB limit on a single cell.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 483,
        "startChar": 31,
        "endLine": 483,
        "endChar": 51
      },
      "revId": "04d80085bb9583d119902dd4f4cfc07138b296af",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fdd3969d_f46bb027",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/specs/specs.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 483,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-12-19T14:24:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My reasoning was that we may have callers who just want to retrieve a single TaskSpec or JobSpec; this implementation makes it possible to do so without having to retrieve the whole thing.  Maybe that\u0027s not worth the cost of having to decode each entry individually?",
      "parentUuid": "e5ed2ec3_a202e7f7",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 483,
        "startChar": 31,
        "endLine": 483,
        "endChar": 51
      },
      "revId": "04d80085bb9583d119902dd4f4cfc07138b296af",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2de97db7_2a6a8a15",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/specs/specs.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 483,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-12-19T15:21:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Another option is to put each TaskSpec or JobSpec in a column rather than a row. It\u0027s pretty easy to select only the columns you want to read. The only advantage of that over one-row-per-spec is your TODO below regarding handling errors -- writes to a single row are atomic.",
      "parentUuid": "fdd3969d_f46bb027",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 483,
        "startChar": 31,
        "endLine": 483,
        "endChar": 51
      },
      "revId": "04d80085bb9583d119902dd4f4cfc07138b296af",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
